## Integration Test Patterns

**Realistic Data Volumes:**
- Test with representative dataset sizes (reference spec.md)
- Example: 50-200 accounts (typical FP&A dataset)
- Measure performance on realistic data

**End-to-End Workflows:**
```python
def test_variance_report_generation_end_to_end():
    """Test complete variance report workflow."""
    # Setup: Create test data files
    budget_file = 'tests/fixtures/budget.xlsx'
    actuals_file = 'tests/fixtures/actuals.xlsx'

    # Execute: Generate report
    report = generate_variance_report(budget_file, actuals_file)

    # Verify: Check report structure
    assert 'Account' in report.columns
    assert 'Budget' in report.columns
    assert 'Actual' in report.columns
    assert 'Variance' in report.columns
    assert 'Variance %' in report.columns
    assert 'Favorability' in report.columns

    # Verify: Check calculations
    first_row = report.iloc[0]
    expected_variance = first_row['Actual'] - first_row['Budget']
    assert first_row['Variance'] == expected_variance
```

