## Testing Anti-Patterns

**❌ Avoid:**
- Testing implementation details (not behavior)
- Brittle tests (break on minor refactors)
- No edge case coverage
- Using float for currency in tests
- Large test fixtures (>1000 rows)
- Slow integration tests (>10 seconds)
- No regression tests after bugs fixed

**✅ Prefer:**
- Testing public interfaces (behavior)
- Resilient tests (refactor-safe)
- Comprehensive edge cases
- Using Decimal in all financial tests
- Small, focused test fixtures
- Fast unit tests (<1 second)
- Regression tests for all bugs

